                                                            </p>
                                                            <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                class="MsoNormal"><strong><em><span
                                                                            style="font-size: 14pt; color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">Embracing
                                                                            Tolerance </span></em></strong><strong><span
                                                                        style="font-size: 14pt; color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">Youth
                                                                        Programme</span></strong></p>
                                                        </span></font>
                                                </span>
                                                <p>&nbsp;</p>
                                                <p style="font-size: 12px; margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                    class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<span
                                                        style="color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">The
                                                        &lsquo;Embracing Tolerance&rsquo; Programme is aimed at 11
                                                        &ndash; 18 year olds and is designed to address Key Stages 3-4
                                                    </span><em><span
                                                            style="color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">diversity</span></em><span
                                                        style="color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">,
                                                        and </span><em><span
                                                            style="color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">personal
                                                            wellbeing </span></em><span
                                                        style="color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">aspects
                                                        of the PHSE/Citizenship programme, and works in harmony with the
                                                    </span><em><span
                                                            style="color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">SEAL
                                                        </span></em><span
                                                        style="color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">initiative
                                                        within the National Curriculum. Furthermore, the programme
                                                        enables schools to meet crucial Ofsted inspection criteria, such
                                                        as </span><em><span
                                                            style="color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">&lsquo;Community
                                                            Cohesion Duty&rsquo;,</span></em><span
                                                        style="color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">
                                                        enhancing &lsquo;</span><span
                                                        style="color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">pupils&rsquo;
                                                        spiritual, moral, social and cultural development&rsquo;
                                                    </span><span
                                                        style="color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">and
                                                    </span><em><span
                                                            style="color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">&lsquo;Judgement
                                                            on Leadership and Management&rsquo; </span></em><span
                                                        style="color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">in
                                                        the way the school </span><em><span
                                                            style="color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">&lsquo;promotes
                                                            equal opportunity and</span></em><span
                                                        style="color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">
                                                    </span><em><span
                                                            style="color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">tackles
                                                            discrimination.&rsquo; </span></em><span
                                                        style="color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">This
                                                        provides an academic context for TIUK to encourage pupils to
                                                        explore attitudes and values and to develop knowledge, skills
                                                        and understanding that support inclusion, challenge racism and
                                                        extremism, and promote diversity. The objective is to bring
                                                        together communities from different races and faiths
                                                        and&nbsp;encourage a shared sense of belonging.</span></p>
                                                <p>&nbsp;</p><strong><span
                                                        style="font-size: 12pt; color: #72a476; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">Social
                                                        Exclusion</span></strong><span
                                                    style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;">
                                                    <font color="#000000"><span
                                                            style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;">&nbsp;
                                                        </span></font>
                                                </span><span
                                                    style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;"></span><span
                                                    style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;">
                                                    <font color="#000000"><span
                                                            style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;">
                                                            <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                class="MsoNormal"><span
                                                                    style="color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">Our
                                                                    programme aims to address problems of social
                                                                    exclusion, which can lead to increasing levels of
                                                                    intolerance, discrimination, bullying, and violent
                                                                    crimes including knifings and gun crime in our
                                                                    schools and on our streets. The main objective of
                                                                    the programme is to improve community relations,
                                                                    promote cohesion and offer a positive alternative to
                                                                    violence. The overall aim is to strengthen and
                                                                    consolidate a shared sense of belonging and
                                                                    community cohesion by bringing together youth from
                                                                    different races, cultures, socio-cultural
                                                                    backgrounds and diverse persuasions. We will achieve
                                                                    this by supporting the youth in changing their
                                                                    attitudes and values, addressing issues of social
                                                                    intolerance and religious extremism, and promoting
                                                                    respect for the diversity of cultures, ethnic groups
                                                                    and nationalities. Social exclusion can also occur
                                                                    when young people feel alienated and polarised due
                                                                    to ethnic and /or religious tensions. These
                                                                    vulnerable young people need a rational
                                                                    counterbalance to help them withstand the influence
                                                                    of extremist groups, who actively recruit
                                                                    disenfranchised young people to support their
                                                                    cause.</span></p>
                                                            <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                class="MsoNormal"><strong><span
                                                                        style="font-size: 12pt; color: #72a476; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">Methodology</span></strong>
                                                            </p>
                                                            <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                class="MsoNormal"><span
                                                                    style="color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">Under
                                                                    the leadership of the Programme Coordinator, a team
                                                                    of volunteers specialising in multicultural and
                                                                    multidisciplinary techniques, will work in close
                                                                    partnership with appropriately religious,
                                                                    educational and community-based agencies. We welcome
                                                                    sensitive partnerships with the police.</span></p>
                                                            <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
                                                            <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                class="MsoNormal"><span
                                                                    style="color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">The
                                                                    programme is delivered through workshops. Using
                                                                    scenarios presenting discriminatory behaviour as
                                                                    initial stimuli, staff will act as facilitators,
                                                                    guiding the students through focused activities,
                                                                    allowing for exploration of prejudice,
                                                                    discrimination and tolerance, and their results on
                                                                    individuals. Diversity will be explored and the
                                                                    audience will be given the opportunity to analyse
                                                                    good practice.</span></p>
                                                            <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                class="MsoNormal"><strong><span
                                                                        style="font-size: 12pt; color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">The
                                                                        learning objectives of the vocational
                                                                        educational </span></strong><strong><span
                                                                        style="font-size: 12pt; color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">programme
                                                                        &quot;</span></strong><strong><em><span
                                                                            style="font-size: 12pt; color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">Embracing
                                                                            Tolerance</span></em></strong><strong><span
                                                                        style="font-size: 12pt; color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">&quot;:</span></strong>
                                                            </p>
                                                            <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                class="MsoNormal"><span>&middot;<strong>Understanding
                                                                        inequalitie</strong></span><span
                                                                    style="color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;"><strong>s</strong></span>
                                                            </p>
                                                            <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                class="MsoNormal"><span
                                                                    style="color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">&middot;</span><strong><span
                                                                        style="color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">Respecting
                                                                        diversities</span></strong></p>
                                                            <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                class="MsoNormal"><span
                                                                    style="color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">&middot;</span><strong><span
                                                                        style="color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">Understanding
                                                                        different c</span></strong><strong><span
                                                                        style="color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">ommunities</span></strong>
                                                            </p>
                                                            <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                class="MsoNormal"><span
                                                                    style="color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">&middot;</span><strong><span
                                                                        style="color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">Developing
                                                                        knowledge of various
                                                                    </span></strong><strong><span
                                                                        style="color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">faiths</span></strong>
                                                            </p>
                                                            <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                class="MsoNormal"><span
                                                                    style="color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">&middot;</span><strong><span
                                                                        style="color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">Learning
                                                                        to be tolerant</span></strong></p>
                                                            <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                class="MsoNormal"><strong><span
                                                                        style="color: #72a476; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">Areas
                                                                        of potential conflict should be examined with a
                                                                        view to offering viable and tolerant
                                                                        alternatives. Staff will provide information
                                                                        regarding the cultures of
                                                                        others.</span></strong></p>
                                                            <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                class="MsoNormal"><strong><span
                                                                        style="font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">(1)Case-study
                                                                        led discussion</span></strong></p>
                                                            <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                class="MsoNormal"><span
                                                                    style="color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">&middot;<span>&nbsp;
                                                                    </span></span><span
                                                                    style="color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">Examining
                                                                    an incident of intolerance or discrimination (for
                                                                    example, of a person or group because of their
                                                                    religious beliefs).</span></p>
                                                            <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                class="MsoNormal"><span
                                                                    style="color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">&middot;<span>&nbsp;
                                                                    </span></span><span
                                                                    style="color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">Imagining
                                                                    in some detail what might be involved for all the
                                                                    participants (perpetrator, bystander and
                                                                    <span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>victim).</span></p>
                                                            <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                class="MsoNormal"><span
                                                                    style="color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">&middot;<span>&nbsp;
                                                                    </span></span><span
                                                                    style="color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">Encouraging
                                                                    participation through the discussion of personal
                                                                    experience,</span></p>
                                                            <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                class="MsoNormal"><span
                                                                    style="color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">&middot;<span>&nbsp;
                                                                    </span></span><span
                                                                    style="color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">Neutrality
                                                                    will be maintained throughout the session, avoiding
                                                                    any moral comment with the aim of understanding the
                                                                    views and opinions of the participants.</span></p>
                                                            <p class="MsoNormal"><strong><span
                                                                        style="font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">(2)
                                                                        Examination of images.</span></strong></p>
                                                            <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                class="MsoNormal"><span
                                                                    style="color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">&bull;
                                                                    Observing images of a variety of people; some
                                                                    represented in the public eye, others unknown to the
                                                                    public.</span></p>
                                                            <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                class="MsoNormal"><span
                                                                    style="color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">&bull;
                                                                    Brainstorming of associations with that image, to
                                                                    examine prejudices and stimulate discussion amongst
                                                                    participants.</span></p>
                                                            <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                class="MsoNormal"><span
                                                                    style="color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">&bull;
                                                                    Discussion of different outcomes, including how
                                                                    stereotypical attitudes portrayed by the media and
                                                                    other sources can influence personal
                                                                    judgements.</span></p>
                                                            <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                class="MsoNormal"><strong><span
                                                                        style="font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">(3)
                                                                        Cross-over role-play.</span></strong></p>
                                                            <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                class="MsoNormal"><span
                                                                    style="color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">&bull;
                                                                    Participants asked to present a situation where some
                                                                    form of intolerance or discrimination can be
                                                                    portrayed (ranging from simple neighbourly or school
                                                                    based disputes to issues concerning racial or
                                                                    religious intolerance or discrimination).</span></p>
                                                            <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                class="MsoNormal"><span
                                                                    style="color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">&bull;
                                                                    Participants asked to take on the roles of those
                                                                    involved, by producing dialogue and acting out
                                                                    scenes, </span><span
                                                                    style="color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">with
                                                                    the goal of finding a positive outcome to overcome
                                                                    discrimination.</span></p>
                                                            <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                class="MsoNormal"><span
                                                                    style="color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">&bull;
                                                                    Done in a cross-over way, so that participants play
                                                                    a non-familiar role. Here moralising, natural
                                                                    comment would be allowed, especially those taken
                                                                    from the perspective of a non-familiar role (i.e.,
                                                                    white/non-white, Muslim/Christian, male/female,
                                                                    etc.)</span></p>
                                                            <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                class="MsoNormal"><strong><span
                                                                        style="color: #72a476; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">W</span></strong><span
                                                                    style="color: #72a476; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">orkshops
                                                                    will last over 1 &ndash; 3 sessions depending upon
                                                                    the audience. We are working towards having our
                                                                    workshops accredited for vocational and educational
                                                                    purposes; as such we seek to have the programme
                                                                    accredited as a Vocationally Recognised
                                                                    Qualification with a view to extending the wider
                                                                    benefits. In association with local schools we are
                                                                    applying our programme to the principles of ASDAN
                                                                    and Citizenship, as required by curriculum
                                                                    standards. We are already working in schools in the
                                                                    London boroughs of Hackney, Tower Hamlets, Enfield
                                                                    and Merton. Our staff will also take on additional
                                                                    service user support roles such as advocacy and
                                                                    sign-posting to other appropriate support agencies
                                                                    where specific needs are identified.</span></p>
                                                            <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                class="MsoNormal"><span
                                                                    style="color: #72a476; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">&nbsp;</span><strong><span
                                                                        style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">Monitoring
                                                                        and Evaluation</span></strong></p>
                                                            <p style="margin-bottom: 0pt; line-height: normal"
                                                                class="MsoNormal"><span
                                                                    style="color: black; font-family: &#39;Trebuchet MS&#39;,&#39;sans-serif&#39;">There
                                                                    will be regular monitoring and evaluation of the
                                                                    programme. Participatory monitoring and evaluation
                                                                    with the beneficiaries will be used to adjust the
                                                                    programme to be more in line with the expectations
                                                                    of the target audience. The programme outcomes will
                                                                    be measured by monitoring:</span></p>
